<% content_for :title, "Langgraph Backend Overview" %>
<% content_for :subtitle do %>
  The AI-powered backend service that generates and manages landing pages for Launch10.
<% end %>

<%= h2_with_anchor "What is Langgraph?" %>

<p>Langgraph is our Node.js/TypeScript backend service that handles all AI-driven operations for Launch10. It's built on LangChain's graph-based orchestration framework and provides:</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>AI-Powered Page Generation</strong> - Creates complete landing pages from user descriptions</li>
  <li><strong>Intelligent Updates</strong> - Modifies existing pages based on natural language instructions</li>
  <li><strong>WebContainer Integration</strong> - Runs generated code in-browser for instant preview</li>
</ul>

<%= h2_with_anchor "Architecture Overview" %>

<p>The Langgraph service is designed as a stateful conversation engine:</p>

<div class="not-prose">
  <pre><code>Rails Frontend (JWT Auth) → Langgraph API → Database
                                    ↓
                              WebContainers
                                    ↓
                              Live Preview</code></pre>
</div>

<%= h2_with_anchor "Key Components" %>

<%= h3_with_anchor "Graphs" %>
<p>Langgraph uses three main graphs to handle different operations:</p>

<ul>
  <li><code>router</code> - Determines which graph to run based on user input</li>
  <li><code>create</code> - Generates new landing pages from scratch</li>
  <li><code>update</code> - Modifies existing pages based on instructions</li>
</ul>

<%= h3_with_anchor "Authentication" %>
<p>The service uses JWT tokens issued by Rails for authentication:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Tokens are validated on every request</li>
  <li>User context is extracted from the JWT</li>
  <li>All resources are scoped to the authenticated user</li>
</ul>

<%= h3_with_anchor "State Management" %>
<p>Langgraph maintains conversation state through:</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Threads</strong> - Conversation contexts linked to Rails projects</li>
  <li><strong>Checkpoints</strong> - Snapshots of conversation state</li>
</ul>

<%= h2_with_anchor "Development Setup" %>

<p>To run the Langgraph service in development:</p>

<div class="not-prose">
  <pre><code># From langgraph_app directory
pnpm install
pnpm run dev
</code></pre>
</div>

<p>The service will be available at <code>http://localhost:2024</code> by default.</p>

<%= h2_with_anchor "Environment Configuration" %>

<p>Copy .env.example to .env and fill in the values:</p>

<div class="not-prose">
  <pre><code>JWT_SECRET=same-as-rails-secret # rails credentials:edit --environment=development
ALLOWED_HOSTS=localhost:3000,127.0.0.1:3000 # Which hosts are allowed to talk to the Langgraph API?
POSTGRES_URI=postgres://localhost/launch10_development 
REDIS_URI=redis://localhost:6379
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...</code></pre>
</div>

<%= h2_with_anchor "Debugging" %>

<p>Open <code>langgraph_app/.env</code> and set <code>NODE_OPTIONS</code> to <code>--inspect-brk</code>, re-run <code>pnpm run dev</code> and open the debugger in your browser or editor.</p>
<p>Common `launch.json` configurations:</p>

<pre><code>
